# Out of Scope (Do Not Build Now)

The following features are planned for V2 or later. Do not implement, scaffold, or design for them in the MVP.

## Explicitly Excluded from MVP
- Crypto / digital asset support
- Portfolio tracking
- Paper trading / simulated trading
- ML models replacing scoring rules
- Advanced alert channels (email, SMS, push)
- Social features (comments, sharing, follows)
- Broker integrations (Alpaca, IBKR, etc.)
- Twitter/X ingestion (deferred to MVP+)
- WebSocket real-time updates (polling is fine for MVP)

## Why This Rule Exists
Scope creep is the primary risk for this project. Every feature added to MVP:
- Increases time to launch
- Introduces more bugs
- Delays validating the core signal accuracy

## If Asked to Add These
Respond with: "This is out of scope for MVP. Log it as a V2 feature."
